[{"question":"Is homosexuality a sin in your eyes?","answer":"Yes, I\u0027ve always believed, Piers -- the Scripture shows that it\u0027s a sin.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":3,"aSentId":4},{"question":"How do you explain a just God can allow this kind of atrocities to happen?","answer":"The world we live in is not a perfect world.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":8,"aSentId":9},{"question":"What is your view of state executions?","answer":"I\u0027m for second chances and mercy.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":10,"aSentId":11},{"question":"If I ask you about abortion, what would you say?","answer":"My view is that every baby should live.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":13,"aSentId":14},{"question":"How could you possibly get any happier?","answer":"Well, you know, I think we all can if we -- if we learned what to ignore and -- you know, certain battles not to fight.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":30,"aSentId":31},{"question":"Why have you selected Friday as a day of great joy and happiness?","answer":"Well, Piers, for the most people, the studies show that people are happier on Fridays.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":38,"aSentId":39},{"question":"Why?","answer":"I think people are looking for the weekends, looking forward to it, getting to relax, you know, done with work and, you know, I\u0027ve also read, Piers, where there\u0027s more heart attacks on Monday than any other day.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":40,"aSentId":41},{"question":"What about the poor guy who\u0027s trapped in a factory job or something or maybe has no job who, just through lack of opportunity and bad circumstance, is unhappy because he can\u0027t get out of that?","answer":"Well, Piers, to me, faith is all about learning to be happy where you are.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":58,"aSentId":59},{"question":"Do you believe, fundamentally, that money can make people happier?","answer":"You know --","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":65,"aSentId":66},{"question":"Victoria, you\u0027re shaking your head, why?","answer":"Well, I mean, it helps -- I mean, it helps but, no, I don\u0027t -- I\u0027ve seen people who are very wealthy and they\u0027re unhappy, they don\u0027t have good relationships.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":67,"aSentId":68},{"question":"Why can poverty stricken people sometimes find joy in their lives?","answer":"I think there\u0027s not so many distractions.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":80,"aSentId":81},{"question":"Or is he always this content happy chap?","answer":"Angry, no.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":88,"aSentId":89},{"question":"When\u0027s the last time you heard him -- when\u0027s the last time you heard him shout, Victoria, come on?","answer":"Never.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":99,"aSentId":100},{"question":"You\u0027ve never heard him shout?","answer":"No, he\u0027s never shouted --","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":101,"aSentId":102},{"question":"He\u0027s never shouted?","answer":"-- and if you -- listen, if you live with me and you don\u0027t shout, you\u0027re pretty good.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":103,"aSentId":104},{"question":"Do you have a temper?","answer":".","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":109,"aSentId":110},{"question":"Do you never shout at anybody?","answer":"No, no, that\u0027s not my personality.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":117,"aSentId":118},{"question":"Let me just clarify, you\u0027ve never shouted in your life?","answer":"Well, I probably have, you know --","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":122,"aSentId":123},{"question":"When was the last time?","answer":"I can\u0027t remember.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":124,"aSentId":125},{"question":"What\u0027s the look?","answer":"It\u0027s like --","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":129,"aSentId":130},{"question":"What can ruin your Friday?","answer":"You know, I don\u0027t know if it would ruin my Friday but I -- like she said, I like things to be right.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":136,"aSentId":137},{"question":"Have you ever had a fist fight?","answer":"I never have -- I never have.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":142,"aSentId":143},{"question":"Not even when you were a kid?","answer":"Well, probably with my brother, yes.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":145,"aSentId":146},{"question":"Never actually -- have you ever been punched in the face?","answer":"No.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":152,"aSentId":153},{"question":"Have you ever been punched in the face?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":158,"aSentId":159},{"question":"You have?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":160,"aSentId":161},{"question":"How do you explain that a just God can allow this kind of atrocities to happen, ruining so many lives?","answer":"You know, it\u0027s difficult, Piers, but the world we live in is not a perfect world.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":178,"aSentId":179},{"question":"Has it ever -- did your faith ever get dented?","answer":"You know, it really --","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":185,"aSentId":186},{"question":"What do you say to people, again, who might come to you and say, I can\u0027t continue having this faith because some appalling thing has happened?","answer":"Yes.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":192,"aSentId":193},{"question":"What do you say to them?","answer":"What I say is this -- God\u0027s got you in the palm of his hand.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":200,"aSentId":201},{"question":"Do you ever watch yourself back on TV?","answer":"I do.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":234,"aSentId":235},{"question":"ORGAN: Do you?","answer":"I do still edit them.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":237,"aSentId":238},{"question":"How have you developed that?","answer":"Well, my mother has had a great memory and when I started, you know, my dad just spoke extemporaneously and just would go and I couldn\u0027t do that.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":244,"aSentId":245},{"question":"What do you think of the whole issue?","answer":"You know, it\u0027s a complicated issue, Piers.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":267,"aSentId":268},{"question":"A life for a life?","answer":"Well, I don\u0027t -- I don\u0027t know that that\u0027s -- you know, I -- it\u0027s -- it\u0027s hard for me.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":272,"aSentId":273},{"question":"And you\u0027ve got to have a view, haven\u0027t you?","answer":"Well, I think the thing is, is we have a justice system and I believe in our system of justice, number one.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":277,"aSentId":278},{"question":"If I asked you about abortion, what would you say?","answer":"Well, abortion, I feel stronger about because it -- I feel like --","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":300,"aSentId":301},{"question":"What\u0027s your view?","answer":"My view is that every baby should live, that, you know, that God\u0027s created that life.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":302,"aSentId":303},{"question":"Should there not be a more consistent view?","answer":"Well, I think there could be when you say may or may not.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":306,"aSentId":307},{"question":"Is homosexuality a sin, in your eyes?","answer":"Yes, I\u0027ve always believed, Piers, the Scriptures shows that it\u0027s a sin.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":322,"aSentId":323},{"question":"What\u0027s your view now?","answer":"You know, Piers, it really never changes because mine was -- mine\u0027s based out of the Scripture.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":330,"aSentId":331},{"question":"I mean, like everything else, doesn\u0027t it have to move with the times and isn\u0027t it down again to people like you to interpret it in a way that evolves when you\u0027re known as a very progressive preacher?","answer":"Sure.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":339,"aSentId":340},{"question":"What if Texas eventually, in a moment, it\u0027s an unlikely place I would imagine to bring this in, but it may change with enough pressure, Texas brings in a law that same-sex marriage is permissible -- how would you feel then if it\u0027s the law of the land?","answer":"Well, you know what, I\u0027m going to respect the law and I\u0027m going to respect gay people like I do now, you know, I have plenty of people that come to our church and friends, I would call, that are gay so I\u0027m going to respect that.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":345,"aSentId":346},{"question":"You could never do that?","answer":"No, it would be against what I believe the scripture teaches and, so, that\u0027s where I think the rub comes in with people like myself.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":348,"aSentId":349},{"question":"I mean, could you ever imagine attending a gay marriage between two people who come to your church, for example, if they invited you?","answer":"Well, I think if it was that easy, that we would have figured it out by now.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":357,"aSentId":358},{"question":"So, would you accept one or not?","answer":".","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":361,"aSentId":362},{"question":"OSTEEN: Would I accept one?","answer":"Two gay people who attend your church invite you to their wedding.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":363,"aSentId":364},{"question":"You would?","answer":"Well, I don\u0027t -- you know, if I had time I would.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":366,"aSentId":367},{"question":"Joel, would you go?","answer":"If they were friends of mine --","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":368,"aSentId":369},{"question":"Could you be seen to do -- could you be photographed at such an event?","answer":"Well, I would not --","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":375,"aSentId":376},{"question":"But of all the Republican runners and riders in the race so far to be the nominee, who do you think is the most impressive leader potentially that you\u0027ve seen?","answer":"Piers, they all look like great leaders to me.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":390,"aSentId":391},{"question":"Really?","answer":"But, I\u0027m -- I\u0027m conservative, you know, that\u0027s who I\u0027ve always been.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":407,"aSentId":408},{"question":"You would say?","answer":"I like to vote on the candidate.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":411,"aSentId":412},{"question":"ORGAN: -- who would it be?","answer":"Good thing I don\u0027t have to right now because it\u0027s too early in the race.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":418,"aSentId":419},{"question":"Is he the kind of guy?","answer":"I like Rick Perry.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":421,"aSentId":422},{"question":"I think -- are you talking about political issues?","answer":"Anything.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":429,"aSentId":430},{"question":"When people come to your church, what are -- what\u0027s really concerning them?","answer":"They care about their relationships -- their relationships, their finances, and their health.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":432,"aSentId":433},{"question":"Do you think politicians, today, are doing the right kind of thing, or are they too busy scuffling with each other in Washington to understand clearly, as you\u0027ve just defined it, what the real issues are for people in America?","answer":"Yes, I think they\u0027re squabbling too much.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":435,"aSentId":436},{"question":"Yes?","answer":"Yes, I think they\u0027re squabbling too much.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":437,"aSentId":438},{"question":"When you see them all ranting and raving and being deliberately obstructive to getting things done, what do you think?","answer":"Well, I think, like most Americans, I would hope that they would work together and, you know, what I -- what I see that\u0027s difficult these days is any kind of compromise and, you know, it\u0027s hard to get 100 percent of what you want.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":442,"aSentId":443},{"question":"Would you be comfortable with that?","answer":"You know what, I\u0027m comfortable with -- that would not stop me from voting for somebody.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":448,"aSentId":449},{"question":"Are there aspects to Mormonism which you find offensive?","answer":"I don\u0027t know a lot about it and here I go again but I don\u0027t know a lot --","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":453,"aSentId":454},{"question":"How can you keep saying that?","answer":"-- I don\u0027t know a lot about it.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":455,"aSentId":456},{"question":"Like what?","answer":"I don\u0027t know -- I don\u0027t --","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":463,"aSentId":464},{"question":"Well, what are the things about Mormonism which are awkward for you?","answer":"You know what, I don\u0027t know enough about their -- their beliefs to -- to point out what they are, to articulate it well.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":469,"aSentId":470},{"question":"Could you vote for a Jewish candidate?","answer":"Sure, I could vote for a Jewish candidate.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":473,"aSentId":474},{"question":"Could you vote for a Muslim candidate?","answer":"Well, I think -- I think I could.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":478,"aSentId":479},{"question":"What do you make of what\u0027s going on with the Palestinians and the Israelis right now?","answer":"Well, it\u0027s a -- it\u0027s a difficult situation.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":482,"aSentId":483},{"question":"You\u0027ve both been out there recently I think, to Israel, right?","answer":"We did.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":488,"aSentId":489},{"question":"How did you find it?","answer":"We found it very peaceful.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":492,"aSentId":493},{"question":"Does it worry you that so many areas of conflict of the world are religion prompted?","answer":"Well, I don\u0027t --","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":502,"aSentId":503},{"question":"If you receive it, can you say amen tonight?","answer":"Amen.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":514,"aSentId":515},{"question":"Do you stop to think, wow, how did this happen?","answer":"I do.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":526,"aSentId":527},{"question":"Am I right to think that the church takes in $18 million a year, but all of that gets plowed back in to the church, is that right?","answer":"That\u0027s correct.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":536,"aSentId":537},{"question":"The books that sell by the squillion, you keep all the cash?","answer":"Well, we give.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":538,"aSentId":539},{"question":"ORGAN: You take some as well?","answer":"Sure.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":541,"aSentId":542},{"question":"Take some of it?","answer":"We do.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":543,"aSentId":544},{"question":"I mean, you\u0027re like multimillionaires, aren\u0027t you?","answer":"Well, we don\u0027t have any problem -- I don\u0027t think God has any problem with you being blessed.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":549,"aSentId":550},{"question":"You like being rich?","answer":"Oh, I like being able to help others.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":555,"aSentId":556},{"question":"You give to people to come to you for help?","answer":"Sure.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":562,"aSentId":563},{"question":"Would you happily write more money to the treasury?","answer":"You know, Piers, again, it\u0027s so far out of my league.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":571,"aSentId":572},{"question":"Not you personally, but do you mind paying more tax?","answer":"Well, I wouldn\u0027t be foolish.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":574,"aSentId":575},{"question":"What I was saying was: would you like it?","answer":"No, I would -- let them have all of the money and the government run great without the money and I give it away to other people.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":580,"aSentId":581},{"question":"What do you think ideologically -- and I ask you, Victoria -- of the principle of rich people paying more tax generally?","answer":"Well, you know, I think they pay a good pay a good amount of tax right now as it is.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":584,"aSentId":585},{"question":"Isn\u0027t it just a convenient thing that rich people come out with?","answer":"You know, I don\u0027t know.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":588,"aSentId":589},{"question":"I think that you know, just like you, you know, do you want to pay more taxes?","answer":"I wouldn\u0027t mind paying more tax.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":593,"aSentId":594},{"question":"It\u0027s a different class structure, isn\u0027t it?","answer":"I think it is.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":603,"aSentId":604},{"question":"Would you be happy with that?","answer":"Oh, I\u0027d be thrilled, you know, nothing greater than for your children to follow in your legacy.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":627,"aSentId":628},{"question":"I mean, are you going to have to keep an extra close eye because you\u0027re the Osteens, everyone be looking to trip them up?","answer":"Oh, you know what, I never feel like it like that.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":634,"aSentId":635},{"question":"What\u0027s he talking about?","answer":"Oh, well, we -- we have good conversations.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":656,"aSentId":657},{"question":"What\u0027s your perfect Friday?","answer":"Well, we like to have a good dinner and we like to either ride our bikes or we like to just hang out and talk or, you know, we may have a few friends over.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":663,"aSentId":664},{"question":"What\u0027s the secret?","answer":"And I respect him even more.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":668,"aSentId":669},{"question":"Yes, what\u0027s the secret of the Joel Osteen magic, you think?","answer":"Well, I think he\u0027s a man of what he -- of his word, I think he\u0027s a man of what his word.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":670,"aSentId":671},{"question":"Do you agree with all that Joel?","answer":"Oh, that and more.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":675,"aSentId":676},{"question":"I mean, you must get some groupies, any?","answer":"Oh, I have some kind people -- I don\u0027t call them groupies -- but people that, you know, they feel like you\u0027ve helped them and you know what, I -- listen --","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":680,"aSentId":681},{"question":"Do you get all that?","answer":"I don\u0027t -- I don\u0027t --","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":683,"aSentId":684},{"question":"Are you like popular like Tom Jones, you know?","answer":"I don\u0027t -- no, not in the work we do.","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":685,"aSentId":686},{"question":"Ever do that?","answer":"Well, I -- you know, it\u0027s funny because when I -- when I\u0027m out, even by myself, this is what women say to me, \"Oh, Victoria, I love your husband.\"","docId":"111008pmt","qSentId":689,"aSentId":690}]